  "text": "Tran et al. [CITATION_1] found constantly elevated HR (heart rate) and VLF (very low frequencies) of HRV (heart rate variability) in AD patients during scratching and also psychological stress. They also report dysfunction of parasympathetic system in acute stress, inferred from HR changes in respiratory frequencies. Higher basal HR in atopic dermatitis was also observed by Seiffert et al. [CITATION_2] . However, though overall HR was higher in AD group, authors also reported lower HR",
